<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.230.103882.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. A, B Bayesian tree inferred from combined plastid (ndhA intron, rps 16 - trnK, rps 16 intron, rps 3, and rpl 32 - trnL) and ITS sequences. Thick branches indicate posterior probabilities of 0.95 - 1; species in bold occur in Central America; Scale bar: 2 %." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/887869" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.230.103882.figure13>
    dc:description "Figure 13. A-G Muhlenbergia rigida (Kunth) Kunth A habit B inflorescence (narrow) C inflorescence (open) D ligule E glumes F floret G stamens and pistil H Muhlenbergia mucronata (Kunth) Trin. H floret. A, B drawn from P. M. Peterson 9659 (US) C-I drawn from P. M. Peterson, C. R. Annable & J. Valdes-Reyna 10876 (ANSM, US) H drawn from P. M. Peterson & C. R. Annable 10778 (US)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/887881" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

